                <h1>Do Hospitals Conduct Background Checks on Visitors?</h1>
                <p>Yes, hospitals typically run background checks on visitors, particularly in sensitive areas like pediatrics or departments dealing with vulnerable populations. These checks help ensure the safety of patients and staff. Visitor policies may vary by institution, so it's advisable to check with the specific hospital for their guidelines.</p>
